The paper deals with algorithms for finger searching in sets, which is a classic data structure problem in computer science. The paper presents new approaches for achieving optimal or near-optimal time bounds for finger searching queries in sets with insertions and deletions. This falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and algorithm analysis and complexity (cs.AL). The paper also involves some probabilistic analysis, which could place it under discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of randomized algorithms could also place it under computational complexity (cs.CC) or numerical analysis (cs.NA).
